					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I just ask because I never really trought about it, and suddently I end up asking myself.<br /><br />I think emulating the CPU should be really easy especially if you're not going to go for cycle accuracy. If you go for cycle accuracy then you need more work as you have to separate all instruction into cycles (instead of executing them as a bulk and advcing the clock of N cycles). Emulating accurately a pipelined CPU should be harder as you have to simulate the hazards, stalls, etc...<br /><br />Emulating audio should be rather easy since you can just reuse parts of an exiting player plugin.<br /><br />The hard part should be doing the graphics. You need to emulate the console's GPU well enough to support most games. I bet the only way is to generate the image pixel by pixel, and then send it to the screen somehow. I never coded anything that's using a GUI so I have no idea how hard this is to do, but it sounds the hardest part.</div>

					
							<br /><br />
