				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Dealing with the OS is always a chore, because the way you do something is mostly arbitrary. Similarly, if the emulated system isn't well-documented, there's lots of trial-and-error, and you're left with emulating the games rather than the system. Another hurdle is getting a clear view of what's going on in your emulator and the emulated system when things aren't working right. It's also good to have a clear idea at the beginning of the scope of your effort, e.g. how accurate, how efficient, what's good enough, what doesn't matter. If you change these as you develop, you might have to redo lots of the program.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

