						<div class="postbody">@Bregalad<br /><br />If you did have a perfectly documented computer in your native language which answered all of your questions without the need for looking elsewhere then the only <em>bottleneck</em> would be something to do with the individual writing the emulator.<br /><br />Lack of confidence, lack of time, poor programming skills, starting a PSX emulator before we can write a NES one etc. are the only kind of problems that I faced when writing my emulator when I started WedNESday since 2003. Back then? I didn't have <em>A F*****G CLUE </em> what the hell I was doing. But 10 years on, all of those problems I just mentioned don't get in my way anymore.<br /><br />Confident? Hell yes. Time? I'm unemployed. Programming skills? Great. So much better than back then but always room for improvement of course. Starting a PSX emulator before you can even write a NES one? Well, I've done my NES one now, almost, and I know now that I can accomplish anything emulator-wise just as long as I am willing to dedicate myself to it AND there is of course, sufficient documentation.</div>

					
